Hypertensive Vascular Disease Symptoms, What Are Symptoms Of Hypertensive Vascular Disease? http://heartnews365.com/detorex33281997 Hypertensive heart disease refers to heart problems that occur because of high blood pressure. These problems include: Coronary artery disease and angina; Heart failure; and Thickening of the heart muscle. High blood pressure means the pressure inside the blood vessels is too high. As the heart pumps against this pressure, it must work harder. Over time, this causes the heart muscle to thicken. Without treatment, symptoms of heart failure may develop. Sometimes the muscle can be so thick that it does not get enough oxygen. This can cause angina. High blood pressure also leads to thickening of the blood vessel walls.
